    This script aims to generate all microservices images (frontend & backend) and launch docker-compose.
        => No need to manually change paths â€“ script is dynamic


Start Script:
    Go to :
        cd C:\Users\StagiaireDEV\Desktop\sneakyDateReforged-v0.1\dockerLaunchGuide
    And run :
        .\sdrBuildAndUp.ps1

    OR double-click on:
            sdrBuildAndUpExecution.bat
    (Go to the dockerLaunchGuide folder through file explorer and click on the sdrBuildAndUpExecution.bat file)





Manual build helper :

    Docker Compose location:
        C:\Users\StagiaireDEV\Desktop\sneakyDateReforged-v0.1\docker-compose\prod

    real-time verification of microservices :
        while ($true) { Clear-Host; docker ps; Start-Sleep -Seconds 1 }


    # Build docker-compose
    cd C:\Users\StagiaireDEV\Desktop\sneakyDateReforged-v0.1\sdr-backend\docker-compose\prod
    docker-compose down
    docker-compose up -d

    # Build image pour ms-configServer
    cd C:\Users\StagiaireDEV\Desktop\sneakyDateReforged-v0.1\sdr-backend\ms-configServer
    mvn clean package -DskipTests
    docker build -t jirawah/ms-configserver:latest .

    # Build image pour ms-eurekaServer
    cd C:\Users\StagiaireDEV\Desktop\sneakyDateReforged-v0.1\sdr-backend\ms-eurekaServer
    mvn clean package -DskipTests
    docker build -t jirawah/ms-eurekaserver:latest .

    # Build image pour ms-auth
    cd C:\Users\StagiaireDEV\Desktop\sneakyDateReforged-v0.1\sdr-backend\ms-auth
    mvn clean package -DskipTests
    docker build -t jirawah/ms-auth:latest .
